<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the Central
                                    American Court of Justice</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Jose</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-23"><hi rend="italic">June 23,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Encouraged by the approval of your excellency’s Government in the matter
                            of mediation in Nicaragua the Central American court has insisted on it
                            and proposed practical means of pacification. American legation here
                            will in due course be informed of the bases.</p>
                        <p>With respectful consideration.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ernesto Martin</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>